{"lemma":"رَخْواتٌ","slug":"رَخْواتٌ","root":"ر.خ.#","root_slug":"ر-خ-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-خ-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n15162","n15168"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%AE%D9%92%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be slack, to be loose"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"slack, loose, yielding, flabby, soft","examples":[{"text":"ويقول فريدلاند إن \"بوتين كحائز على الحزام الأسود في الألعاب القتالية لايرى في أساسات الديمقراطية مثل حرية التعبير وسيادة القانون إلا وسائد هوائية رخوة تصلح للتدرب عليها في تنفيذ الركلات\".\nAnd Freedland says that “Putin, possessing a black-belt in fighting, doesn’t see in tenets of democracy like freedom of expression and rule of law anything but slack airbags fit for training to kick on them.”\nparaphrasing Jonathan Freedland on The Guardian: We have to see through Putin’s fog of lies, and take action now:\nHe has shown us how he sees, for example, the basic tenets of democracy – whether that’s free speech or belief in the rule of law, evidence and due process. To us, those may look like the firm pillars that hold up a decent society. But to a black-belt such as Putin they are rotten timbers, ripe for a good kicking and liable to bring down the whole edifice."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"fricative","examples":[{"text":"ومنها الرِّخْوَةُ وهي: الهاء، والحاء، والغين، والخاء، والشين، والصاد، والضاد، والزاي، والسين ،والظاء، والثاء، والفاء. وذلك إذا قلت الطَّسْ وانْقَضْ وأشباه ذلك أجريتَ فيه الصوت إن شئت."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n15162","headword_ar":"رَخُوَ","root":"rxw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaroxuw","text_ar":"يَرْخُو"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raxiYa","text_ar":"رَخِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaroxaY","text_ar":"يَرْخَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, Msb, K;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raxaAwapN","text_ar":"رَخَاوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raxaA='N","text_ar":"رَخَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K, but in several copies of the latter"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raxFA","text_ar":"رَخًا"},{"kind":"text","text":",) or this is a simple subst., (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rixowapN","text_ar":"رِخْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, (M, K,) which is extr., (M,) and some add"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruxowapN","text_ar":"رُخْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raxowapN","text_ar":"رَخْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MF, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, soft, yielding, flaccid, flabby, lax, slack, uncompact, crummy, fragile, frangible, brittle, friable, easily"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickly broken; i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAra rixowFA","text_ar":"صَارَ رِخْوًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~aA","text_ar":"هَشَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAna","text_ar":"لَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstrxY","text_ar":"استرخى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (S,* K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raxuwa","text_ar":"رَخُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raxiYa","text_ar":"رَخِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) and ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raxaA","text_ar":"رَخَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEaA","text_ar":"دَعَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of which the aor. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadoEuw","text_ar":"يَدْعُو"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raxaA","text_ar":"رَخَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raEaY","text_ar":"رَعَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of which the aor. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaroEaY","text_ar":"يَرْعَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; in the CK, erroneously, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruEiYa","text_ar":"رُعِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K, TA;) the aor. [or the first and third] being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaroxuw","text_ar":"يَرْخُو"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [that of the second and fourth being]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaroxaY","text_ar":"يَرْخَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) said of life ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayo$","text_ar":"عَيْش"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, ample, unstraitened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plentiful, in its means,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumstances:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K: *) or said of a man, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raxaA='N","text_ar":"رَخَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, in an ample, an unstraitened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a plentiful, state of life."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK.)"}],"source_refs":["M","Msb","K","S","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n15168","headword_ar":"رِخْوٌ","root":"rxw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raxowN","text_ar":"رَخْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruxowN","text_ar":"رُخْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Msb, K;) but accord. to As and Fr, the first is that which is approved, (TA,) or, accord. to Az, it is that used by the Arabs; (Msb;) the second, accord. to As and Fr (TA) and Az, (Msb,) being post-classical; (Msb, TA;) and the third is of the dial. of the Kilábees; (Msb;) applied to a thing (S, K) of any kind, (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Soft, yielding, flaccid, flabby, lax, slack, uncompact, crummy, fragile, frangible, brittle, friable, easily"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickly broken;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$~u","text_ar":"هَشُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lay~anN saholN","text_ar":"لَيَّنٌ سَهْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotaroxK","text_ar":"مُسْتَرْخٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same, as is shown by the explanation of its verb in the first sentence of this art.:] the fem. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rixowapN","text_ar":"رِخْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raxowapN","text_ar":"رَخْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruxowapN","text_ar":"رُخْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotaroxiyapN","text_ar":"مُسْتَرْخِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HajarN rixowN","text_ar":"حَجَرٌ رِخْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raxowN","text_ar":"رَخْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruxowN","text_ar":"رُخْوٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stone that is soft, yielding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasN rixowapN","text_ar":"فَرَسٌ رِخْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mare that is easy, and gentle, moderate, deliberate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leisurely, in pace."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasN rixowu AlEinaAni","text_ar":"فَرَسٌ رِخْوُ العِنَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse that is easy to be led,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tractable."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) The phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fahiYa rixowN","text_ar":"فَهِىَ رِخْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in a verse of Aboo-Dhu-eyb instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fhY rixowapN","text_ar":"فهى رِخْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"because meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fahiYa $aYo'N","text_ar":"فَهِىَ شَىْءٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rixowN","text_ar":"رِخْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHuruwfu Alr~ixowapu","text_ar":"الحُرُوفُ الرِّخْوَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which may be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lax letters"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said in the K, by an anticipation of the pen, to be applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the letters exclusive of those comprised in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo yuroEuwnaA","text_ar":"لَمْ يُرْعُونَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for which some say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo yarowi Ean~aA","text_ar":"لَمْ يَرْوِ عَنَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: Sgh says [correctly] that they are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the letters exclusive of those termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~adiydapu","text_ar":"الشَّدِيدَةُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and of those in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lm yrEwnA","text_ar":"لم يرعونا"},{"kind":"text","text":": as is said in the M, they are thirteen; namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"v","text_ar":"ث"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"x","text_ar":"خ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*","text_ar":"ذ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"z","text_ar":"ز"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$","text_ar":"ش"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"D","text_ar":"ض"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Z","text_ar":"ظ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"g","text_ar":"غ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [to which De Sacy adds, in his Grammar, (2nd ed. i. 29,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", which are generally included in an intermediate class between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$dydp","text_ar":"شديدة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rxwp","text_ar":"رخوة"},{"kind":"text","text":", namely, in the class consisting of the letters in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lm yrEwnA","text_ar":"لم يرعونا"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lm yrw En~A","text_ar":"لم يرو عنّا"},{"kind":"text","text":":] the letter termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rixowN","text_ar":"رِخْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is that in which the sound runs on, as it does, for instance, in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$","text_ar":"ش"},{"kind":"text","text":"when you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almas~","text_ar":"المَسّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~a$~","text_ar":"الرَّشّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Lth","S","M","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}